buildPostRequest

public HttpRequest buildPostRequest(JsonRpcRequest request)
Builds a POST HTTP request for the JSON-RPC requests objects specified in the given JSON-RPC request object.

You may use JsonHttpParser.parserForResponse(execute (request)) to get the JsonParser, and Json.parseAndClose(JsonParser, Class, CustomizeJsonParser) .

Parameters:
request - JSON-RPC request object
Returns:
HTTP request

buildPostRequest

public HttpRequest buildPostRequest(List<JsonRpcRequest> requests)
Builds a POST HTTP request for the JSON-RPC requests objects specified in the given JSON-RPC request objects.

Note that the request will always use batching -- i.e. JSON array of requests -- even if there is only one request. You may use JsonHttpParser.parserForResponse(execute (requests)) to get the JsonParser, and Json.parseArrayAndClose(JsonParser, Collection, Class, CustomizeJsonParser) .

Parameters:
requests - JSON-RPC request objects
Returns:
HTTP request

buildGetRequest

public HttpRequest buildGetRequest(JsonRpcRequest request)
                            throws IOException
Builds a GET HTTP request for the JSON-RPC requests objects specified in the given JSON-RPC request object.

You may use JsonHttpParser.parserForResponse( executeUsingGet (request)) to get the JsonParser, and Json.parseAndClose(JsonParser, Class, CustomizeJsonParser) .

Parameters:
request - JSON-RPC request object
Returns:
HTTP response
Throws:
IOException - I/O exception
